result.execSummary:
The defendant James T. Love was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 3:56 pm case called. Defendant James T. Love in court with attorney John B. Selsing.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached-argued sentence.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Guilty to both counts.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright the repeater enhancers.  Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Selsing. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to-Count 1-12 months WCJ,  STAYED and places on probation for a period of 24 months. CONDITIONS: Timely payments of Child Support as ordered in 07PA42.  Maintain employment. Address with DA & Child Support. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Terms of Agent. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given. Count 2- SWD and places on probation for 24 months, concurrent. Same Conditions as Count 1.
